zcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Local Assemblies limited'''\n| 23 March 2020\n| From 24 March onwards (replaced from 7 April onwards).\n| '''Local assemblies only online'''\nMunicipal and regional assemblies shall convene only for necessary purposes (measures regarding COVID-19 or necessary to prevent other damages) and shall take place only online. Recommendation to broadcast online assemblies publicly on the internet. \n| Government Resolution No. 274 published as No. 122/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"23 March Resolutions\">{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38821 |title=23 March resolutions |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 6 April 2020\n| From 7 April until the end of State of Emergency\n| '''Local assemblies subject to social distancing'''\nMunicipal and regional assemblies shall convene in a way that ensures distance of 2 metres between each individual. Everyone present must wear face cover.\n\nRecommendation to allow participation through means of distance communication.\n| Government Resolution No. 388 published as 151/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"third travel ban\" />\n|-\n| Electronic data boxes use for free\n| 23 March 2020\n| From 24 March onwards (until the end of State of Emergency).\n| \"Electronic data boxes\" is a secure means of online communication run by the Government that may be used for formal delivery of documents. Normally only communication with authorities is free while communication between private entities is subject to a fee. This fee was waived until the end of the State of Emergency.\n| Government Resolution No. 275/2000 Coll.<ref name=\"23 March Resolutions\"/>\n|-\n\n<!--\n\nH A R D ---------------------------------------- M E A S U R E S\n\n-->\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=6 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Hard measures'''\n| {{No|'''STATE OF EMERGENCY'''}}\n| {{No|Declaration of State of Emergency. For the first time in modern history for the area of entire country (previously only regionally, mainly due to floods).\n\nA number of other particular measures announced at the same time under Government emergency powers (see elsewhere in the table).}}\n| {{No|12 March 2020}}\n| {{No|From 12 March 2020 2&nbsp;pm for a period of 30 days.\n\n'''Extended by [[Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic|Chamber of Deputies]] until 30 April.'''}}\n| {{No|[[Government of the Czech Republic|Government]] (cabinet headed by [[Prime Minister of the Czech Republic|Prime Minister]]) has considerably extended powers under the State of Emergency. State of Emergency may be declared by Government for at most 30 days; any extension must be ratified by Chamber of Deputies.\n\n'''Most other measures adopted \"indefinitely\" remain in force only as long as the State of Emergency lasts, as without it the Government lacks the constitutional authority to limit the associated rights.'''}}\n| {{No|Government Resolution No. 194/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"State of Emergency\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/Usneseni-vlady-k-vyhlaseni-nouzoveho-stavu.pdf |title=State of Emergency |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nVote number 8 of 43rd meeting of Chamber of Deputies held on 7 April 2020<ref name=\"autogenerated2\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.psp.cz/sqw/hlasy.sqw?G=72491 |title=Hlasov\u00e1n\u00ed Poslaneck\u00e9 sn\u011bmovny \u2013 43/8 |publisher=Psp.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 369 published as No. 156/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"auto1\">https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38837</ref>}}\n|-\n| Border enforcement\n| Provisional enforcement of borders with Germany and Austria and limitations on international flights. Only selected border crossings remain open:\n* Germany (unlimited): Str\u00e1\u017en\u00fd, Pomez\u00ed nad Oh\u0159\u00ed, Rozvadov, Folmava, \u017delezn\u00e1 Ruda, Kr\u00e1sn\u00fd Les, Hora Svat\u00e9ho \u0160ebesti\u00e1na\n* Germany (limited to regulars only, e.g. cross-border workers, etc.; 5 AM to 11 PM): V\u0161eruby, Ji\u0159\u00edkov, Vojtanov, C\u00ednovec\n* Austria (unlimited): Doln\u00ed Dvo\u0159i\u0161t\u011b, \u010cesk\u00e9 Velenice, Hat\u011b, Mikulov\n* Austria (limited to regulars only, e.g. cross-border workers, etc.; 5 AM to 11 PM):Vrat\u011bn\u00edn, Valtice, Nov\u00e1 Byst\u0159ice\n* International flights only to/from V\u00e1clav Havel International Airport and Kbely Airport (both near Prague), other airports limited to domestic flights.\n| 12 March 2020\n| From 14 March 2020 onwards.\n| Czech Republic is a party to [[Schengen Treaty]] and does not normally enforce its border with other EU countries.\n| Government Resolution No. 197/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"borders limited\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/Opatreni-o-docasnem-znovuzavedeni-ochrany-vnitrnich-hranic-CR_1.pdf |title=Borders limited |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=4 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''BORDERS CLOSURE'''\n| {{No|'''Crossborder public transport ban'''}}.\n| 12 March 2020\n| From 14 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Any road vehicle with a capacity of more than 9 people (incl. driver) banned from crossing borders with an exemption of (1) larger vehicles bringing Czech citizens or long-term/permanent residents to the Czech Republic, (2) larger vehicles taking foreigners out of the Czech Republic (exemption: empty buses, passenger trains, and ships may return to the Czech Republic).\n\nCrossborder passenger rail and passenger ship transport banned.\n\nOnly V\u00e1clav Havel Prague International Airport may be used for international flights.\n\nAn individual exemption may be granted by the Minister of Transportation.\n| Government Resolution No. 200/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"public transport cross border ban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/Opatreni-v-mezinarodni-osobni-doprave_1.pdf |title=Opatrina |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Travel ban \u2013 selected countries'''\n| 12 March 2020\n| From 14 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n\n'''Effectively replaced by complete travel ban from 16 March onwards''' (see below).\n| Foreigners coming in from selected countries banned from entering the Czech Republic (foreigners with long-term or permanent residency permits exempted). \n\nCzech citizens and foreigners with long-term or permanent residency banned from entering selected countries. \n\nSuspension of processing of all visa applications (individual exceptions possible).\n\nList of selected countries subject to daily updates, as of the day of ban entry into force they were '''China, South Korea, Iran, Italy, Spain, Austria, Germany, Switzerland, Sweden, Norway, the Netherlands, Belgium, Great Britain, Denmark, and France'''.\n| Government Resolution No. 198/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"travel ban limited\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/Opatreni-o-zakazu-vstupu-do-CR-a-cestovani-do-rizikovych-zemi_1.pdf |title=Limited travel ban |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''COMPLETE BORDERS CLOSURE'''}}\n* Czech citizens:\n** Not allowed to leave the country unless they have long-term or permanent residency abroad.\n** May return to the country; subject to mandatory 14 days' self-quarantine (see above).\n* Foreigners with long-term or permanent residency:\n** Allowed to leave the country.\n** May return to the country if they were outside when measure adopted; subject to mandatory 14 days' self-quarantine (see above).\n** May not return to the country if left while the measure was in force.\n* Foreigners without long-term or permanent residency:\n** Allowed to leave the country.\n** Not allowed to enter the country.\n| 13 March 2020\n| From 16 March onwards (ban of 13 March).\n\nFrom 31 March until 12 April 2020 (ban of 30 March).\n\nExtended until 13 April 2020 (ban of 6 April).\n| Exemptions:\n\n* '''International freight transport''': drivers, flight crews, train crews, ship crews. Exempt also freight transport workers employed abroad.\n* Diplomatic staff.\n* Emergency services while on duty (police, EMT, fire, mountain rescue, etc.).\n* People who verifiably periodically cross borders, especially '''workers''' with a place of employment no further than 100 kilometres from the border.\n* Citizens of Germany, Austria, Poland and Slovakia who verifiably periodically cross borders, especially workers with a place of employment no further than 100 kilometres from the border.\n* Epidemiology, humanitarian and health experts.\n* Members of the European Parliament.\n* Minors who are citizens of an EU member state with at least one parent who is a Czech citizen.\n* Persons transporting blood, bone marrow and/or organs for purpose of transplantation.\n* Persons with a serious medical condition for purpose of undertaking medical procedures abroad.\n| Government Resolution No. 203<ref name=\"complete travel ban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_203.pdf |title=Complete travel ban |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> & Ministry of Interior Notice on Exemptions from travel restrictions during the State of Emergency<ref name=\"min interior notice on exemptions\"/> (until 30 March)\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 334 published as 142/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"travel ban no 2\">{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38829 |title=Travel ban |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> (from 31 March)\n|-\n| {{No|'''BAN ON ENTRY OF FOREIGNERS'''}}\n* Foreigners without long-term or permanent residency:\n** Allowed to leave the country.\n** Not allowed to enter the country.\n\n* Leaving country allowed only if the travel is in accordance with conditions of curfew (see above) and purpose of travel cannot be fulfilled within the Czech Republic\n| 6 April 2020\n| From 14 April until the end of State of Emergency\n| Exemptions:\n\n* '''International freight transport''': drivers, flight crews, train crews, ship crews. Exempt also freight transport workers employed abroad.\n* Diplomatic staff.\n* Persons who periodically cross borders for work reasons\n* Epidemiology, humanitarian and health experts.\n* Other in case of urgent reasons\n\nAnyone coming into Czech Republic has duty to contact health authority and will be subject to mandatory 14 days quarantine (with exemptions).\n| Government Resolution No. 387 published as No. 150/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"third travel ban\">{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38834 |title=Third travel ban |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n<!--\n\nO T H E R ---------------------------------------- M E A S U R E S\n\n-->\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=19 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Other measures'''\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Army deployed'''\n| Army units deployed to support border enforcement (see above). \n| 10 March 2020\n| From 10 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely). \n| 2,100 Czech Army personnel ordered to full readiness.\n\nArmy also used for distribution of medical equipment around country (respirators etc.).\n| Government decision<ref name=\"army deployed\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mocr.army.cz/informacni-servis/zpravodajstvi/armada-podpori-jednotky-izs-na-hranicnich-prechodech-219873/|title=Arm\u00e1da podpo\u0159\u00ed jednotky IZS na hrani\u010dn\u00edch p\u0159echodech|website=mocr.army.cz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.natoaktual.cz/armada-koronavirus-covid-metnar-hranice-vlada-opatreni-pij-/na_zpravy.aspx?c=A200313_210710_na_zpravy_m00|title=Arm\u00e1da po\u0161le kv\u016fli koronaviru na hranice a\u017e 2 100 voj\u00e1k\u016f \u2013 Natoaktual.cz|date=13 March 2020|website=natoaktual.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''Soldiers deputised'''}}\n| 15 March 2020\n| From 15 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n| 2,096 soldiers and 432 Customs officers deputised for police duty. Previously, they could serve only in support role. This allows a significantly lower number of police officers to be deployed at the borders and their redeployment back to standard policing duty.\n\n'''9 April 2020''': Number of deputised soldiers increased to 4,094.\n| Government Regulation No. 83/2020 coll.<ref name=\"army deputized\">{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38810 |title=Info |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nGovernment Regulation No. 155/2020 Coll.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://aplikace.mvcr.cz/sbirka-zakonu/ViewFile.aspx?type=c&id=38836 |title=Info |publisher=aplikace.mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Release of emergency funding\n| CZK 500 million released from Government Emergency Fund for emergency purchases of medical tools needed to fight COVID-19.\n| 13 March 2020\n|\n|\n| Government Resolution No. 206/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"500 million\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_206.pdf |title=Info |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Provision of welfare\n| {{No|'''Students of secondary and tertiary schools welfare programmes compelled to work duty, actual work subject to later call-up.'''\n\nWelfare providers are ordered to provide welfare to recipients whose life or health may be in jeopardy (providers cannot refuse provision of welfare).}}\n| 13 March 2020\n| From 16 March onwards (indefinitely).\n| Welfare provision aimed at persons that are not self-sufficient (elderly, crippled, etc.).\n| Government Resolution No. 207/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"welfare\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_207.pdf |title=Data |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=5 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Social and economical support measures'''\n| '''Trucks allowed to drive on Sundays'''\n| 13 March 2020\n| From 13 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n| Generally, freight trucks are banned from driving on Sundays to ease weekend return traffic. This long-standing ban was lifted to mitigate possible freight disruptions stemming from other measures or general COVID-19 impact.\n| Government Resolution No. 205/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"trucks on sundays\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_205.pdf |title=Trucks on Sundays |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Income tax deadline extended\n\nDeadline for Income Tax submission moved by 3 months for natural persons (new date is 1 July)\n| 12 March 2020\n|\n|\n| {{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n|-\n| Loans repayment delayed\n\nBanks will provide an option of delaying loan payments for people and small businesses affected by the coronavirus\n| 12 March 2020\n|\n|\n| {{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n|-\n| Gun sales registration period waived. \n| 16 March 2020\n| From 16 March until end of the curfew\n| In general, purchased firearms must be physically presented to the police for registration within 10 days from the sale (see [[Gun laws in the Czech Republic]]). Firearm sales still possible when delivered directly to customers' homes.\n\nFirearm registrations deemed non-essential by the Ministry of Interior Explanatory Note, as part of the general suspension of non-essential visits to government offices. Gun licence holders instructed to merely inform police about a purchase by post or electronic communication and visit station for registration after the end of curfew.\n\nAlso, exams required for new firearm licences suspended. New permits to purchase B-category firearms issued only remotely (by post or electronic communication). \n| Ministry of Interior Explanatory Note No. MV- 49249-2/OBP-2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mvcr.cz/soubor/zajistovani-spravnich-cinnosti-v-oblasti-zbrani-v-dobe-nouzoveho-stavu.aspx |title=Zajistovani |publisher=mvcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Forestry short-term hiring \n| March 2020\n| 2020 forestry season\n| Public company {{Interlanguage link|Lesy \u010cesk\u00e9 republiky|cs|Lesy \u010cesk\u00e9 republiky}} which manages public forests started massive short-term hiring of people from professions affected by quarantine measures. Temporary workers take part in restoration of spruce forests that suffered large scale damage by bark beetle and drought in previous years. Wage of CZK 120 per hour (ca \u20ac5 per hour), contracts for maximum of 300 hours per person.\n|<ref>{{cite web|author=V\u010dera 14:56Stanislav Pt\u00e1\u010dn\u00edk<!-- -->, Pr\u00e1vo |url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/praci-v-lesich-nasly-stovky-brigadniku-40319850 |title=Pr\u00e1ci v les\u00edch na\u0161ly stovky brig\u00e1dn\u00edk\u016f |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Criminal sanctions\n| COVID-19 added to list of diseases the wilful spreading of which constitutes a felony. \n| 13 March 2020\n|\n| '''Up to 10 years imprisonment in case of criminal negligence.'''\n|Government Resolution No. 210/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"criminal sanctions\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/DOC130320-130320_210.pdf |title=Aktualne |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=9 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Healthcare provision support measures'''\n| {{No|'''Drive-through testing'''}}\n| 14 March 2020\n|\n| \"Drive-through\" tents set up in front of designated hospitals around the country. Patients don't need to leave their cars to be tested.\n\nTesting is free for people with prescriptions by the health authorities. Prescriptions are granted remotely (phone and email) based on symptoms and travel history. People lacking prescriptions may pay for their own tests. Prices vary depending on the hospital from CZK 1,300\u20133,000 (\u20ac50\u2013120). Some drive-through locations do not offer paid testing due to capacity limitations (i.e. they test only those with a prescription).\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blesk.cz/clanek/zpravy-koronavirus/637593/zmatek-v-testovani-na-nakazu-covid-19-vysetreni-si-muzete-zaplatit-v-peti-laboratorich.html|title=Koronavirus: Laborato\u0159e, kter\u00e9 mohou testovat a kde si m\u016f\u017eete test zaplatit|website=Blesk}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''COVID-19-only hospitals'''\n| 15 March 2020\n|\n| Two hospitals, {{Interlanguage link|Na Homolce Hospital|cs|Nemocnice Na Homolce}} in the capital and largest city of Prague, {{Interlanguage link|St. Anna University Hospital|cs|Fakultn\u00ed nemocnice u sv. Anny v Brn\u011b}} in the second largest city of Brno, were designated to deal with COVID-19 only. Both cities have several other hospitals to take up the caseload of other conditions.\n\nMilitary [[Biosafety level|BSL-4 reserve hospital]] at Biological Defense Center in [[T\u011bchon\u00edn]] put into a state of readiness.\n| {{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n|-\n| 28 March 2020\n|\n| After COVID-19 infection spread in at least seven retirement homes, several hundred beds were set aside for quarantine and treatment of elderly with mild symptoms at:\n* Na Bulovce hospital in Prague\n* Na Franti\u0161ku hospital in Prague\n* Health resort at [[L\u00e1zn\u011b Tou\u0161e\u0148]]\n* Non-emergency section of Military BSL-4 reserve hospital at Biological Defense Center in T\u011bchon\u00edn\n| Ministry of Health decision<ref>{{cite web|author=Adam Vojt\u011bch@adamvojtechano |url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/zpravy-domov/domovy-pro-seniory-vyhrazena-luzka-v-nemocnicich-techonin-seniori-karantena-adam_2003281300_vtk |title=Ministerstvo vy\u010dlen\u00ed v nemocnic\u00edch stovky l\u016f\u017eek pro naka\u017een\u00e9 seniory. Aktivuje i T\u011bchon\u00edn &#124; iROZHLAS \u2013 spolehliv\u00e9 zpr\u00e1vy |publisher=Irozhlas.cz |date=28 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''Medicine students' work duty'''}}\n| 15 March 2020\n| From 16 March until the end of State of Emergency\n| 5th- and 6th-year students of General Medicine compelled to work duty, actual work subject to later call-up.\n\nLast-year students of nursing, paramedics, and several other related fields compelled to work duty, actual work subject to later call-up.\n| Government Resolution No. 220 published as No. 90/2020 Coll.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://apps.odok.cz/attachment/-/down/IHOABMRE46CG |title=Data |publisher=apps.odok.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 404 published as No. 158/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n|-\n| Healthcare workers' holiday ban\n| 23 March 2020\n| From 24 March until the end of State of Emergency\n\n'''Revoked on 10 April 2020.'''\n| Healthcare workers banned from taking a holiday (time off).\n| Government Resolution No. 278 published as 125/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"23 March Resolutions\"/>\n\nGovernment Resolution No. 403 published as No. 157/2020 Coll. (revocation)<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n|-\n| '''Remdesivir provisional approval'''\n| 17 March 2020\n| From 17 March for a period of 9 months\n| [[Remdesivir]], originally developed by [[Gilead Sciences]] for [[ebola]] treatment, was approved for experimental use for COVID19 patients in serious condition.\n| Ministry of Health Decision No. MZDR 12059/2020-3/OLZP<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40603&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20LP%20Remdesivir.pdf |title=Remdisivir |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| '''Plaquenil prescription restrictions'''\n| 23 March 2020\n| From 23 March 8&nbsp;pm onwards (indefinitely)\n| [[Hydroxychloroquine]], sold under the brand name Plaquenil among others, is a medication used for the prevention and treatment of certain types of malaria. Plaquenil showed promise in some COVID-19 trials. Only doctors with selected specialisations can prescribe it under the measure.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12756/2020-2/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40681&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20p%C5%99edepisov%C3%A1n%C3%AD%20l%C3%A9%C4%8Div%C3%A9ho%20p%C5%99%C3%ADpravku%20Plaquenil%2023.%203.%202020.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> (until 3 April)\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12756/2020-3/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40852&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20p%C5%99edepisov%C3%A1n%C3%AD%20l%C3%A9%C4%8Div%C3%A9ho%20p%C5%99%C3%ADpravku%20Plaquenil.pdf |title=Info |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> (after 3 April)\n|-\n| '''Hydroxychloroquine-sulfaat teva provisional approval'''\n| 7 April 2020\n| From 7 April for period of 8 months\n| Provisional approval for COVID-19 treatment due to plaquenil shortage.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 13360/2020-3/OLZP<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40885&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20LP%20HYDROXYCHLOROQUINE-SULFAAT%20TEVA.pdf |title=HYDROXYCHLOROQUINE-SULFAAT |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12756/2020-3/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/> (after 3 April)\n|-\n| Hospitalised patients' information database\n| 24 March 2020\n| From 24 March onwards (indefinitely)\n| Central database about COVID-19 hospitalised patients. Hospital providers ordered to:\n* insert data about the state of hospitalised COVID-19 patients daily\n* insert data about every new patient that gets either to serious condition, requires ventilator or ECMO within one hour\n* insert data about every patient whose state changes as regards serious condition, use of ventilator or ECMO within one hour\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12996/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40693&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20z%C3%A1znam%20o%20hospitalizovan%C3%A9m%20pozitivn%C3%ADm%20n%C3%A1lezu%20v%20ISIN.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Interpersonal solidarity==\n[[File:Ochrann\u00e1 rou\u0161ka, n\u00e1vod.webm|right|thumb|Demonstration of making facemasks without sewing]]\n\nThe COVID-19 pandemic in the Czech Republic has created a wave of solidarity in a variety of areas, including:\n* Due to the lack of protective face-masks, volunteers sewed masks for other people and also shared instruction videos online.<ref>{{cite web|author=Autor ave, kac zdroj: \u010cT24, Ministerstvo zdravotnictv\u00ed |url=https://ct24.ceskatelevize.cz/domaci/3063778-jak-si-vyrobit-nouzovou-rousku-bez-siti-socialni-site-radi-kus-latky-ministerstvo-i |title=Jak si vyrobit nouzovou rou\u0161ku bez \u0161it\u00ed? Soci\u00e1ln\u00ed s\u00edt\u011b rad\u00ed kus l\u00e1tky, ministerstvo i pap\u00edrov\u00fd kapesn\u00edk \u2014 \u010cT24 \u2014 \u010cesk\u00e1 televize |publisher=Ct24.ceskatelevize.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Programmes were launched to help the most vulnerable groups and seniors, on a non-commercial basis, by buying food and medicines.<ref>{{cite web|author=Michal Burda |url=https://zlinsky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/pomoc-nejohrozenejsim-seniorum-privezou-nakupy-az-domu-20200318.html |title=Pomoc nejohro\u017een\u011bj\u0161\u00edm: senior\u016fm p\u0159ivezou n\u00e1kupy a\u017e dom\u016f \u2013 Zl\u00ednsk\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Zlinsky.denik.cz |date=18 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* On Monday, 23 March, [[Czech Television|Czech National Television]] launched a temporary new television channel \u010cT3, which is to bring practical advice, news and a selection of \u010cT's classic programmes from the archive for older people.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskatelevize.cz/porady/10000000408-naladte-se-na-ct3/ |title=Nala\u010fte se na \u010cT3 \u2014 \u010cesk\u00e1 televize |publisher=Ceskatelevize.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* The Vietnamese community in the [[\u00dast\u00ed nad Labem]] region raised CZK 140,000 for a donation of a ventilator to a hospital in \u00dast\u00ed nad Labem<ref>{{cite web|author=Janni Vorl\u00ed\u010dek |url=https://ustecky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/vietnamska-komunita-se-slozila-na-plicni-ventilatory-pro-usteckou-nemocnici-20200323.html |title=Vietnamsk\u00e1 komunita se slo\u017eila na plicn\u00ed ventil\u00e1tory pro \u00fasteckou nemocnici \u2013 \u00dasteck\u00fd den\u00edk |publisher=Ustecky.denik.cz |date=23 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n* Due to the closure of Czech schools, Czech National Television launched an educational programme for home education. The \"U\u010d\u00edTelka\" programme is focusing on teaching first-grade pupils. The programmes \"Odpoledka\" on teaching second-grade pupils and programme \"\u0160kola doma\" for ninth grade pupils preparing them for entrance exams to secondary schools.<ref>{{cite web|author=16. 3. 2020, 10:52Jana Perglov\u00e1<!-- -->, Pr\u00e1vo |url=https://www.novinky.cz/domaci/clanek/ceska-televize-zacina-ucit-deti-zakladnich-skol-40316814 |title=\u010cesk\u00e1 televise za\u010d\u00edn\u00e1 u\u010dit d\u011bti z\u00e1kladn\u00edch \u0161kol |publisher=Novinky.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Czech manufacturer of 3D printers [[Prusa Research]] contributed to the \"free use project\" of shared Bicycles company [[Rekola]] to enable access to transport with a lower risk of virus transmission than public transport.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/prusa-research-a-boj-s-koronavirem-jak-je-dulezite-byt-pripraven/ |title=Prusa Research a boj s koronavirem: jak je d\u016fle\u017eit\u00e9 b\u00fdt p\u0159ipraven \u2013 Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny Josef Prusa \u2013 3D tisk a tisk\u00e1rny |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date=19 March 2020 |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> Prusa Research also designed, produced and distributed protective face shields for medical professionals.<ref>{{cite web|author=Josef Pr\u016f\u0161a |url=https://josefprusa.cz/od-navrhu-k-hromadnemu-3d-tisku-zdravotnickych-stitu-behem-tri-dnu/ |title=Aktualizov\u00e1no 30.3. \u2013 Od n\u00e1vrhu k hromadn\u00e9mu 3D tisku zdravotnick\u00fdch \u0161t\u00edt\u016f b\u011bhem t\u0159\u00ed dn\u016f |publisher=Josefprusa.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The \u017duf\u00e1nek family distillery from [[Bor\u0161ice]] will produce and distribute for free disinfectant gels without the necessary permit from the health and agriculture department.<ref>{{cite web | title=Zak\u00e1zali mi vyr\u00e1b\u011bt dezinfekci, st\u011b\u017euje si \u017duf\u00e1nek. O povolen\u00ed nest\u00e1l, \u0159\u00edkaj\u00ed celn\u00edci | website=Aktu\u00e1ln\u011b.cz \u2013 V\u00edte, co se pr\u00e1v\u011b d\u011bje | date=23 March 2020 | url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/ekonomika/zufanek-dezinfekce/r~84235f126d0611ea80e60cc47ab5f122/ | language=cs | access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Let\u00e1k_MZCR_Coronavirus_A5.pdf|Information flyer from the Ministry of Health sent to every house address \nFile:Usnesen\u00ed vl\u00e1dy k vyhl\u00e1\u0161en\u00ed nouzov\u00e9ho stavu.pdf|Government Resolution on Declaration of Emergency\nFile:COVID-19_Czech_Government_SMS_notification_about_shop_shutdown.jpg|SMS notification of the closure of shops\nFile:Celetn\u00e1 ulice bez turist\u016f 2020 03 203.jpg|Prague, Celetn\u00e1 ulice, without tourists(March 2020)\nFile:Starom\u011bstsk\u00fd orloj bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|Prague, Astronomical clock, without spectators (March 2020)\nFile:V\u00e1clavsk\u00e9 n\u00e1m\u011bst\u00ed bez turist\u016f 2020 03 23.jpg|thumb|Prague, Wenceslas Square, without tourists (March 2020)\nFile:Praha Flora karant\u00e9na b\u0159ezen 2020.jpg|Prague, Flora shopping centre (March 2020)\nFile:No entry to driver's area in Brno city transport due to COVID-19 (detail).jpg|Brno, forbidden to enter front section of local bus. (March 2020)\nFile:Westfield Chodov NCOV-19.jpg|Empty shopping mall in the Czech Republic during COVID-19 pandemic\nFile:Autobus, nevstupovat k \u0159idi\u010di (01).jpg|Interior of a Czech bus during COVID-19 pandemic (14 March 2020)\nFile:Antonov Airlines Antonov An-124-100 Vanzura-2.jpg|Antonov An-124-100 similar aeroplanetype which provided medical products purchased by the Czech government in China\nFile:Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9, drive-trhu COVID-19 testing.jpg|Drive thru testing centre at the University Hospital Hradec Kr\u00e1lov\u00e9\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Healthcare in the Czech Republic]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19/ Actual Situation Dashboard Ministry of healthcare]\n* [https://www.datawrapper.de/_/Sgf7v/ Epidemic curve from countries including the Czech Republic]\n* [https://covid-19-cz.chcepe.now.sh/ Interactive map of COVID-19 situation in the Czech Republic]\n* [https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n* [https://theenewstimes.com/corona-virus-live-statistics/ Live Statistics of Corona-virus on the World Map]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable standard floatleft\" style=\"text-align:left;margin-top: 12px;\"\n|+\n!Information from the Ministry of Health of the Czech Republic \u2013 COVID-19\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/seznam-odberovych-center/ Hospitals with COVID-19 testfacility \u2013 Blue is with self-pay testfacility]\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/seznam-laboratori/ List of laboratories testing on COVID-19 in Czech Republic]\n|-\n|[https://koronavirus.mzcr.cz/en/ Important-phone-numbers and links// Emergency contact numbers]\n|-\n! Most services are available 24h and seven days a week\n|}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Czech Republic|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Czech Republic|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in the Czech Republic}}\n{{bare URLs|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak Czechia per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million residents by region\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Czech Republic]]\n| first_case      = Unknown\n| arrival_date    = 1 March 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days\n | month1 = 03\n | day1   = 1\n | year1  = 2020\n | month2 = \n | day2   = \n | year2  = }} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], Hubei, China via Italy\n| recovery_cases  = 527<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| deaths          = 147<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 6,059<ref name=\":0\"/>\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://onemocneni-aktualne.mzcr.cz/covid-19}}\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] saw its first three confirmed cases in the [[Czech Republic]] on 1 March 2020. On 12 March, the government declared a [[state of emergency]], for the first time in the country's modern history for the area of the entire country. On 16 March, the country closed its borders, forbade the entry of foreigners and issued a nationwide curfew. While originally planned until 24 March, the measures were later extended until 1 April<ref name=\"apnews\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/breaking/czech-republic-severely-limits-freedom-of-movement-in-order-to-slow-down-coronavirus-spread|title=Czech Republic goes into quarantine to slow down coronavirus spread|website=Radio Prague International|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> and then again until the end of State of Emergency<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /> which was extended by the [[Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic|Chamber of Deputies]] until 30 April 2020.<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.psp.cz/eknih/2017ps/stenprot/043schuz/s043037.htm#h8 |title=P\u010cR, PS 2017 , 43. sch\u016fze, \u010d\u00e1st 37 (7. 4. 2020) |publisher=Psp.cz |date= |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nCzech Republic started gradual easing of measures from 7 April 2020 onwards.<ref name=\"third travel ban\" /><ref name=\"sports allowed\" />\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |date= |publisher=Government of the United Kingdom |url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |date= |website=wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/The Czech Republic medical cases chart}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:80%; float:right; clear:right; margin:0 0 0.5em 1em;\"\"\n|+COVID-19 cases in the Czech Republic<ref name=\":0\"/>\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Date\n! colspan=\"2\" | Confirmed\n! colspan=\"2\" | Recovered\n! colspan=\"2\" | Deaths\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Active<br / >cases\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Tested<br/>(Total)\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Detected<br/>ratio\n|-\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n! New\n! Total\n|-\n! 28 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 193\n| \n|-\n! 29 February\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 0\n| 200\n| \n|-\n! 1 March\n| 3 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 211\n| {{#expr:3/(211-200)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 2 March\n| 0 || 3\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 3\n| 262\n| {{#expr:0/(262-211)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 3 March\n| 2 || 5\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 5\n| 340\n| {{#expr:2/(340-262)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 4 March\n| 0 || 5\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 5\n| 407\n| {{#expr:0/(407-340)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 5 March\n| 3 || 8\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 8\n| 483\n| {{#expr:3/(483-407)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 6 March\n| 11 || 19\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 19\n| 594\n| {{#expr:11/(594-483)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 7 March\n| 7 || 26\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 26\n| 787\n| {{#expr:7/(787-594)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 8 March\n| 6 || 32\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 32\n| 928\n| {{#expr:6/(928-787)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 9 March\n| 6 || 38\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 38\n| 1,193\n| {{#expr:6/(1193-928)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 10 March\n| 25 || 63\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 63\n| 1,358\n| {{#expr:25/(358-193)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 11 March\n| 31 || 94\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 94\n| 1,816\n| {{#expr:31/(816-358)*100 round 2}}%\n|-\n! 12 March\n| 22 || 116\n| 0 || 0\n| 0 || 0\n| 116\n| 2