ct to following conditions (cumulative):\n* Only geolocation data of COVID19-positive person,\n* '''only subject to such person's explicit consent''' which may be taken back at any time,\n* geolocation data for previous three weeks,\n* data may be used only for purpose of epidemiologic tracing,\n* health authority may store the original data only for necessary period of time, no more than 6 hours.\n\nGeolocation data is used to draft a map of COVID19 person's movement in previous days. This map is then presented to the person to help them remember who they were in contact with, where and when. Identified contacts are then put into 14 days quarantine.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12398/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref>https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40616&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20na%C5%99%C3%ADzen%C3%AD%20pro%20oper%C3%A1tory%20ve%C5%99ejn%C3%BDch%20mobiln%C3%ADch%20komunika%C4%8Dn%C3%ADch%20s%C3%ADt%C3%AD%20a%20banky.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| Soldiers deployed to reinforce health authority.\n| 30 March 2020\n| From 30 March 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n| 300 soldiers (mainly paramedics and students of [[University of Defence (Czech Republic)|Military University of Medicine]]) deployed to reinforce health authority for the purpose of tracing contacts of COVID-19 positive patients and for collecting their samples.\n| Government Resolution No. 333 published as No. 141/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"travel ban no 2\"/>\n|-\n| '''Special requirements for release from preventative quarantine.'''\n| 9 April 2020\n| From 16 April 2020 onwards (indefinitely).\n| People who were put into quarantine due to previous contact with COVID-19 positive person may be released from quarantine only if (cumulatively):\n* 14 days elapsed,\n* lack of COVID19 symptoms, unless those can be attributed to other illness,\n* negative outcome of rapid test on COVID19 antibodies,\n* negative outcome of test for IgM a IgG antibodies.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15757/2020-6/MIN/KAN<ref>https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40920&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20ukon%C4%8Dov%C3%A1n%C3%AD%20karant%C3%A9ny.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| Hospital visits ban.\n| Ban on visits in hospitals and similar facilities. Exemptions for visits to patients who are (1) minors, (2) legally incapacitated, (3) pregnant or (4) terminally ill.\n| 9 March 2020\n| From 10 March onwards (indefinitely).\n|\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10519/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"hospital visits ban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/ministerstvo-zdravotnictvi-zakazuje-navstevy-vsem-poskytovatelum-zdravotnich-slu_18682_4107_1.html|title=Ministerstvo zdravotnictv\u00ed zakazuje n\u00e1v\u0161t\u011bvy v\u0161em poskytovatel\u016fm zdravotn\u00edch slu\u017eeb l\u016f\u017ekov\u00e9 p\u00e9\u010de a za\u0159\u00edzen\u00edm soci\u00e1ln\u00edch slu\u017eeb|website=mzcr.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Public gatherings banned'''.\n| Gatherings of '''100 or more people''' banned.\n| 10 March 2020\n| From 10 March 6&nbsp;pm onwards (indefinitely).\n| Ban on private and public gatherings of 100 or more people, including theatres, music events, cinemas, sports, etc. Exemptions for (1) legislature, (2) executive government, (3) courts and (4) public or private assemblies mandated by law (e.g. shareholder meetings)\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 10666/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"100 people ban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/mimoradna-opatreni-ministerstva-zdravotnictvi-zakazuji-konani-hromadnych-akci-na_18698_4107_1.html|title=Mimo\u0159\u00e1dn\u00e1 opat\u0159en\u00ed Ministerstva zdravotnictv\u00ed zakazuj\u00ed kon\u00e1n\u00ed hromadn\u00fdch akc\u00ed nad 100 osob i v\u00fduku na \u0161kol\u00e1ch|website=mzcr.cz}}</ref>\n|-\n| Gatherings of '''30 or more people''' banned.\n| 12 March 2020\n| From 13 March 6&nbsp;pm onwards (indefinitely).\n| Ban on any private and public gatherings of 30 or more people. Exemptions for (1) legislature, (2) executive government, (3) courts, (4) public assemblies mandated by law and (5) funerals.\n| Government Resolution No. 199/2020 Coll.<ref name=\"30 people ban\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vlada.cz/assets/media-centrum/aktualne/Opatreni-o-zakazu-poradani-kulturnich--sportovnich-a-dalsich-akci-s-ucasti-nad-30-osob_1.pdf |title=Opatreni |publisher=vlada.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|Gatherings of '''more than 2 people''' banned.}}\n| 23 March 2020\n| From 23 March until 1 April.\n\nExtended until 11 April.\n\nExtended until end of State of Emergency.\n| Ban on any gathering at the publicly accessible place of more than 2 people. Exemptions for (1) members of same household, (2) exercise of profession and (3) funerals as long as a distance of 2 metres between people is kept.\n| Ministry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12745/2020-1/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"2 people ban\"/>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 12745/2020-4/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"2 people ban 2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40761&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20prodlou%C5%BEen%C3%AD%20omezen%C3%AD%20pohybu%20osob.pdf |title=Data |publisher=mzcr.cz |date= |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nMinistry of Health Protection Measure No. MZDR 15190/2020-5/MIN/KAN<ref name=\"curfew 10 April\">https://www.mzcr.cz/Soubor.ashx?souborID=40922&typ=application/pdf&nazev=Mimo%C5%99%C3%A1dn%C3%A9%20opat%C5%99en%C3%AD%20-%20z%C3%A1kaz%20voln%C3%A9ho%20pohybu%20osob,%20s%20vyjimkami.pdf</ref>\n|-\n| {{No|'''Schools suspended.'''}}\n| All pupils and students banned from personally attending classes (including university lectures). Staff may continue to work and assign homework for students.\n\nKindergartens and creches remain open.\n| 10 March 2020\n| From 11 March 