{"title_page": "Kentucky\u2013Louisville rivalry", "text_new": "{{short description|Sports rivalry between the Universities of Kentucky and Louisville}}\n \n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2017}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox sports rivalry\n| wide                  = yes\n| name                  = Kentucky\u2013Louisville rivalry\n| image                 = \n| image_size            = \n| caption               = \n| team1                 = [[Kentucky Wildcats]]\n| team1logo             = Kentucky Wildcats logo.svg\n| team2                 = [[Louisville Cardinals]]\n| team2logo             = Louisville Cardinals wordmark.svg\n| sport                 = [[college basketball|basketball]], [[college football|football]], others\n| firstmeeting          = \n| mostrecent            = \n| nextmeeting           = \n| total                 = \n| series                = \n| largestvictory        = \n| longeststreak         = \n| longestunbeatenstreak = \n| currentstreak         = \n| currentunbeatenstreak = \n| trophy                = \n| trophy series         = \n| stadiums              =  \n}}\n{{OSM Location map        \n| coord = {{coord|38.112|-85.225}}\n| zoom = 7\n| width = 295 \n| height = 250\n| caption = Locations of Kentucky and Louisville\n| mark1 = Blue pog.svg\n| label1 = Kentucky\n| mark-coord1 = {{coord|38.033333|-84.5}}\n| label-pos1 = top\n| label-color1 = black\n| mark2 = Red pog.svg\n| label2 = Louisville\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|38.2527|-85.7585}}\n| label-pos2 = top\n| label-color2 = black\n}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:right; clear:right; margin-left:1em; font-size:88%;\"\n|+ College Comparison\n! \n! style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Kentucky Wildcats}}\" | [[University of Kentucky|{{white|Kentucky}}]]\n! style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Louisville Cardinals}}\" | [[University of Louisville|{{white|Louisville}}]]\n|-\n! scope=row | Founded\n| align=center | 1865 || align=center | 1798\n|-\n! scope=row | Type \n| align=center | [[Public university|Public]] || align=center |[[Public university|Public]]\n|-\n! scope=row | Location\n| align=center |  [[Lexington, Kentucky|Lexington]] || align=center | [[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville]]\n|-\n! scope=row | Conference \n| align=center |  [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]] || align=center | [[Atlantic Coast Conference|ACC]]\n|-\n! scope=row | Students \n| align=center | 29,182 || align=center | 22,640\n|-\n! scope=row | School colors \n| align=center | {{color box|#0033A0}} {{color box|White}} || align=center | {{color box|#C9001F}} {{color box|Black}}\n|-\n! scope=row | Nickname \n| align=center |  [[Kentucky Wildcats|Wildcats]] || align=center | [[Louisville Cardinals|Cardinals]]\n|-\n! scope=row | Stadium\n| align=center | [[Kroger Field]] || align=center | [[Cardinal Stadium]]\n|-\n! scope=row | Arena\n| align=center | [[Rupp Arena]] || align=center | [[KFC Yum! Center]]\n|}\nThe '''Kentucky\u2013Louisville rivalry''' refers to the rivalry between the University of Kentucky Wildcats (Kentucky) and the University of Louisville Cardinals (Louisville). The Kentucky\u2013Louisville rivalry is one of the most passionate rivalries, especially in men's [[college basketball]]. It is considered one of the most intense rivalries in the NCAA. The intensity of the rivalry is captivated by the proximity of the two schools and the state of Kentucky's interest in college sports (no pro-affiliated sports teams play in the state of Kentucky).\n\n==Men's basketball==\n{{Main|Kentucky Wildcats men's basketball|Louisville Cardinals men's basketball}}\n{{Infobox sports rivalry\n| wide                  = yes\n| name                  = Kentucky\u2013Louisville men's basketball rivalry\n| image                 = \n| image_size            = \n| caption               = \n| team1                 = Kentucky Wildcats\n| team1logo             = Kentucky Wildcats logo.svg\n| team2                 = Louisville Cardinals\n| team2logo             = Louisville Cardinals wordmark.svg\n| sport                 = Basketball\n| firstmeeting          = February 15, 1913<br />Kentucky 34, Louisville 10\n| mostrecent            = December 28, 2019<br />Kentucky 78, Louisville 70\n| nextmeeting           = 2020-21 Season - Louisville, KY<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://watchstadium.com/future-college-basketball-non-conference-schedules-for-2020-and-beyond-11-20-2019/|title=Future College Basketball Non-Conference Schedules for 2020 and Beyond|last=Wittry|first=Andy|website=Watch Stadium|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n| total                 = 52\n| series                = Kentucky leads, 37\u201316 Regular season and 2 NCAA\n| largestvictory        = Kentucky: 34 points (1948)<br />Louisville: 22 points (1988)\n| longeststreak         = \n| longestunbeatenstreak = \n| currentstreak         = Kentucky, 3 (2017\u2013present)\n| currentunbeatenstreak = \n| trophy                = \n| trophy series         = \n| stadiums              =  \n}}\n\nThe Kentucky\u2013Louisville rivalry has been ranked the 2nd best rivalry in college basketball by Bleacher Report and 3rd best rivalry in all of college sports by [[List of members of the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame|Basketball Hall of Fame]] contributor [[Dick Vitale]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/espn/dickvitale/story/_/id/7561633/dick-vitale-picks-best-rivalries-college-sports|title=Dick Vitale picks the best rivalries in college sports|publisher=ESPN}}</ref> Kentucky and Louisville first played against each other in 1913 but stopped playing each other in the 1920s, playing only twelve times between 1913 and 1983. The rivalry was generally dormant with only occasional matchups until the teams met in the [[1983 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament|1983 NCAA Tournament]].  Since then, the two teams have met each year in late December or early January.\n\nMuch like the [[Iron Bowl]], the Kentucky\u2013Louisville rivalry is all the more intense because the two schools have consistently been among the nation's elite men's basketball teams for most of the last 50 years.  Both schools are also two of the most victorious programs in [[NCAA]] men's basketball history; Kentucky is #1 on the list of all-time [[List of teams with the most victories in NCAA Division I men's college basketball|winningest program]]s in [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]] Men's Basketball and Louisville #26.  Kentucky has eight national championships and Louisville three, although one was later vacated by the NCAA.  Both schools also sit in the top ten of men's basketball teams that have had athletes to be picked in the first round of the NBA draft. Kentucky has had 46 players selected in the first round, while Louisville has had 24.\n\n===History===\nThe rivalry was fueled when [[Rick Pitino]] was hired as Louisville's head men's basketball coach in 2001. He served in that same role with Kentucky from 1989 to 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/03/22/sports/college-basketball-louisville-hires-pitino-to-spice-a-rivalry.html|title=Louisville Hires Pitino To Spice A Rivalry|date=March 22, 2001|work=The New York Times}}</ref> In the time that Rick Pitino was the head coach at Louisville from 2001 to 2017, Kentucky has won 12 of its contests and Louisville has won 6 of its contests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/sports/college/louisville/2018/12/27/louisville-kentucky-rivalry-every-basketball-game-score/2416024002/|title=See the scores of every Louisville-Kentucky basketball game in history|last=Lerner|first=Danielle|website=The Courier-Journal|language=en|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> Kentucky leads the all-time series with Louisville 37-16, and Kentucky leads the modern series 28-13.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.bigbluehistory.net/bb/Statistics/Louisville.html|title = Kentucky's Record versus Louisville|publisher=Big Blue History|accessdate = September 16, 2007}}</ref>  In six tournament meetings as of 2014, Kentucky leads the series four games to two with their most recent win coming in the 2014 sweet sixteen 74-69. The teams met in the [[2012 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|2012 Final Four]], and Kentucky defeated Louisville with a score of 69-61 en route to the national title. This was the deepest ever tournament meeting between the two schools and their first tournament meeting since 1984.\n\n{{clear}}\n\n===Results===\nRankings are from the [[AP Poll]] (1936\u2013present)\n\n{{sports rivalry series table\n| legend_forfeit_text = Vacated wins{{#tag:ref|Louisville has vacated all of its victories from the 2011\u201312, 2012\u201313, 2013\u201314, 2014\u201315 seasons. These 123 wins are not included in Louisville's all-time record, nor are the victories against Kentucky during this span counted in the series record between the two teams.<ref name=\"Sanctions\">[https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2018/02/20/louisville-basketball-will-vacate-2013-national-championship-as-ncaa-upholds-ruling/]. ''[[The Washington Post]]'', 2018-02-20.</ref>|group=\"n\"|name=\"vacation\"}}\n| format = compact| cols = 2\n| team1 = Kentucky\n| team1style = {{NCAA color cell|Kentucky Wildcats}}\n| team2 = Louisville\n| team2style = {{NCAA color cell|Louisville Cardinals}}\n| series_summary = yes\n\n| February 15, 1913 | [[Lexington, KY]] | Kentucky | 34 | Louisville | 10\n| February 7, 1914 | Lexington, KY | Kentucky | 22 | Louisville | 17\n| March 3, 1914 | [[Louisville, KY]] | Kentucky | 26 | Louisville | 13\n| January 23, 1915 | Lexington, KY | Kentucky | 18 | Louisville | 14\n| February 27, 1915 | Louisville, KY | Kentucky | 15 | Louisville | 26\n| February 12, 1916 | Lexington, KY | Kentucky | 22 | Louisville | 28\n| February 22, 1916 | Louisville, KY | Kentucky | 32 | Louisville | 24\n| January 17, 1922 | Louisville, KY | Kentucky | 38 | Louisville | 14\n| January 21, 1922 | Lexington, KY | Kentucky | 29 | Louisville | 22\n| [[1948 NCAA Basketball Tournament|March 27, 1948]]<sup>A</sup> 